# 'ls' color definitions for use with 'dircolors' to support
# 5250_terminal.py "magic cookie dough" attributes.
#
# NOTE: Only apply these definitions when running under
# 5250_terminal.py - e.g. check $TERM in your shell initialization
# script before calling dircolors - as no TERM statements are used
# below.
#
# See the dir_colors(5) man page for a description of the format of
# this file.

# There is no way to unset a value from its default or set it to an
# empty string, so set these to sequences which 5250_terminal.py
# ignores:
LEFTCODE  \e[?2004h
RIGHTCODE \e[?2004h
NORMAL    \e[?2004h

# 'ls' outputs this at the start of the first line, but not subsequent
# lines, messing up column alignment both with 'ls' and 'ls -l'.
# ls_wrapper.py works around this.
ENDCODE φΚ·ϊ # normal

FILE φΚ·ϊ # normal
LINK φΚ·Α # underline
EXEC φΚ·ό # intensity
DIR  φΚ·Γ # intensity, underline

# Not a lot of thought has been put into the following assignments.

ORPHAN  φΚ·Θ # underline, blink
MISSING φΚ·ϊ # normal
FIFO    φΚ·ΐ # reverse
SOCK    φΚ·ΐ # reverse
DOOR    φΚ·ΐ # reverse
BLK     φΚ·ύ # intensity, reverse
CHR     φΚ·ύ # intensity, reverse

SETUID φΚ·│ # intensity, reverse, column separators
SETGID φΚ·▒ # reverse, column separators
STICKY φΚ·░ # column separators
STICKY_OTHER_WRITABLE φΚ·┤ # underline, column separators
OTHER_WRITABLE        φΚ·▓ # intensity, column separators
